        "text": "# Plan: Evolving the SOP Library Manager\n\n## Context\n\nYou have **two sources** that need to be reconciled:\n\n| Source | Location | What It Defines |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Current README.md** | `skills/sop_library_manager/README.md` | Existing implementation — upload/parse/sync with flat tables (`sop_executive_checklists`, `sop_detailed_steps`, `sop_recommended_videos`) |\n| **sop.md** (Claude command) | `.claude/commands/sop.md` (Windows) | Richer architecture — `sop_sections`, `sop_steps`, `sop_dependencies`, `sop_embeddings` + hybrid git→DB sync pipeline |\n\n> ⚠️ I can't access the Windows path directly. I'm working from the content you pasted in your message. If there's more in `sop.md` you'd like me to see, please paste it or copy it into the project.\n\n---\n\n## Part 1: What sop.md Adds That README.md Lacks\n\n### 1A. Richer Schema Model\n\n**Current (README.md):**\n```\nsops → sop_executive_checklists  (flat phase/step/task)\n     → sop_detailed_steps        (flat section/step/content)\n     → sop_recommended_videos    (flat title/url/phase)\n     → sop_sync_log              (audit)\n```\n\n**Proposed (sop.md):**\n```\nsops → sop_sections     (purpose, scope, safety, tools, procedure, troubleshooting...)\n     → sop_steps        (phase_name, phase_number, step_number, step_name, tasks_summary, detail_md)\n     → sop_dependencies (prerequisite, sub-procedure, optional, cross-reference)\n     → sop_embeddings   (pgvector for RAG/AI retrieval)\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- `sop_sections` replaces the implicit section structure with explicit typed sections — enables full-text search per section type\n- `sop_steps` unifies executive checklists + detailed steps into one table with richer metadata — each row becomes a RAG chunk\n- `sop_dependencies` is entirely new — models the Mermaid dependency graphs already in the SOPs\n- `sop_embeddings` is entirely new — enables semantic search via pgvector\n\n### 1B. Hybrid Git→DB Architecture\n\nThe README currently describes: **file → Supabase Storage → parse → DB**\n\nsop.md proposes: **git (source of truth) → parse → DB (serving layer)** with:\n- Git for authoring, version history, review workflow\n- DB for app queries, AI retrieval, real-time work order state\n- GitHub Action pipeline: `git push → parse markdown → upsert → re-embed → update dependencies`\n\n### 1C. Work Order Integration\n\nThis is the critical missing piece. sop.md explicitly calls out:\n- Work orders referencing `sop_id` \n- Step completion tracking against `sop_steps`\n- Field worker app serving SOPs on mobile\n- AI agents querying step content for dispatch\n\n---\n\n## Part 2: How This Changes the Schema\n\n### Current Schema (migration `20260228000001_sop_library.sql`)\n```sql\nsops (id, sop_number, trade_code, trade_name, task_name, revision, ...)\nsop_executive_checklists (sop_id, section_type, step_number, step_name, tasks, is_checked)\nsop_detailed_steps (sop_id, section_type, section_number, step_number, step_title, content)\nsop_recommended_videos (sop_id, title, url, procedure_phase, sort_order)\nsop_sync_log (sop_id, sop_number, action, details)\n```\n\n### Proposed Evolved Schema\n\n```sql\n-- 1. ENHANCED MASTER TABLE\nsops (\n  id, sop_number, trade_code, trade_name, task_name,\n  revision, status, effective_date, description, scope,\n  est_duration_min, est_duration_max,  -- NEW: from sop.md\n  storage_path, file_hash, tags,\n  organization_id,                      -- NEW: tenant scoping\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- 2. REPLACES executive_checklists + detailed_steps\nsop_sections (\n  id, sop_id, section_number,\n  section_type,  -- 'purpose'|'scope'|'safety'|'tools'|'procedure'|'troubleshooting'|'videos'|...\n  title,\n  content_md,    -- original markdown\n  content_plain, -- stripped text for full-text search\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- 3. UNIFIED STEP TABLE (replaces both checklist + detailed)\nsop_steps (\n  id, sop_id,\n  phase_name,      -- 'removal', 'insta