        "text": "# Plan: SOP System Evolution + Work Order Integration\n\nNow that I have the full `sop.md` command, here's the complete picture and my recommendation.\n\n---\n\n## What sop.md Adds to the README\n\nThe Claude command defines a **7-step authoring workflow** with concepts the current skill doesn't handle:\n\n| Concept | In README? | In sop.md? | Impact |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| REF docs (trade-level shared references) | ❌ | ✅ Step 4 | SOPs use pointer links instead of duplicating PPE/codes/personnel |\n| SOP_INDEX.md as master registry | Mentioned | ✅ Steps 2,3,6 | Planned → Active lifecycle, prerequisite/sub-procedure tracking |\n| Trade folder organization | ❌ | ✅ Step 5 | `docs/sop/{TRADE}/SOP_{TRADE}_{Task}.md` |\n| REF doc registration in index + authoring guide | ❌ | ✅ Step 4 | Cross-document consistency maintenance |\n| Exact 15-section SOP structure with REF pointers | Partial | ✅ Step 5 | Sections 3,4,5,cleanup use `See REF_...` pointers |\n| Executive Checklist max 7 steps rule | ❌ | ✅ Step 5 | Split into sub-phases if >7 |\n| Video placeholder pattern | ❌ | ✅ Step 5 | `🔍 *Video to be sourced*` |\n| Planned entry workflow | ❌ | ✅ Step 3 | Reserve SOP number before authoring |\n\n---\n\n## The Core Architecture Question\n\nYou have two hierarchies that need to work together:\n\n```\nSOP Hierarchy (authoritative procedures):\n  REF Doc (trade-level)  ←  shared PPE, codes, personnel\n    └── SOP (task-level)  ←  procedure phases, steps, checklists\n\nWO Hierarchy (editable work instances):\n  System WO Template  →  Company WO  →  Project WO  →  Unit WO\n  (S-SOP)               (COW)          (PWO)          (DWO)\n```\n\n### Three Options\n\n#### Option A: Separate but Linked\n```\nsop_steps (canonical)  ←──FK──  work_order_tasks (customized copy)\n```\nSOPs and WOs are separate tables. WO tasks are copies that can diverge. Reconciliation = diff.\n\n**Pro**: Clean separation, SOPs are pure reference docs  \n**Con**: Data duplication, reconciliation is complex\n\n#### Option B: SOPs ARE the System WO Templates\n```\nwork_order_templates (scope='system') = SOP content\n  └── company WO inherits\n      └── project WO inherits\n          └── unit WO inherits\n```\nNo separate SOP tables. The system-level WO template IS the SOP.\n\n**Pro**: Single hierarchy, no reconciliation needed  \n**Con**: Loses SOP-specific structure (REF docs, sections, videos, dependencies). WO templates become bloated.\n\n#### Option C: SOPs as Source of Truth, WOs Reference + Override ⭐ RECOMMENDED\n```\nsop_steps (canonical procedure)     work_order_templates.definition\n  │                                   │\n  │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐  │\n  └──│  sop_id FK on WO template   │──┘\n     │  Each WO step references     │\n     │  an sop_step_id + allows     │\n     │  local overrides in JSONB    │\n     └─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Architecture (Option C)\n\n### Why This Works\n\n1. **SOPs stay rich** — full sections, REF doc pointers, videos, dependencies, embeddings\n2. **WOs stay light** — each level just stores overrides/customizations, not full procedure copies\n3. **Each WO level is editable** — company can customize steps, project can further customize, unit can mark not_required\n4. **SOP reference is always available** — field worker sees both the canonical SOP step AND any local modifications\n5. **Reconciliation is trivial** — compare WO override JSONB against current sop_step content; flag diffs\n\n### Schema Design\n\n```sql\n-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════\n-- SOP TABLES (source of truth, git-synced)\n-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\n-- Master SOP record (enhanced from current)\nsops (\n  id uuid PK,\n  sop_number text UNIQUE,        -- 'PLB-SOP-001'\n  trade_code text,               -- 'PLB'\n  trade_name text,               -- 'Plumbing'\n  task_name text,\n  revision text,\n  status text,                   -- 'draft'|'active'|'archived'\n  est_duration_min int,          -- NEW\n  est_duration_max int,          -- NEW\n  ref_doc_id uuid,               -- NEW: FK → sop_ref_docs\n  storage_path text,\n  file_hash text,\n  tags text[],\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- NEW: Trade-level reference documents\nsop_ref_docs (\n  id uuid PK,\n  doc_id text UNIQUE,            -- 'REF-PLB-001'\n  trade_code text,\n  trade_name text,\n  revision text,\n  content_md text,               -- full markdown\n  storage_path text,\n  file_hash text,\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- REPLACES: sop_executive_checklists + sop_detailed_steps\nsop_sections (\n  id uuid PK,\n  sop_id uuid FK → sops,\n  section_number int,\n  section_type text,             -- 'purpose'|'scope'|'safety'|'tools'|'procedure'|...\n  title text,\n  content_md text,\n  content_plain text,            -- for tsvector search\n  is_ref_pointer boolean,        -- true if section says \"See REF doc\"\n  ref_section text,              -- which REF section it points to\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- UNIFIED step table (each row = one RAG chunk = one trackable unit)\nsop_steps (\n  id uuid PK,\n  sop_id uuid FK → sops,\n  section_id uuid FK → sop_sections,  -- which procedure section\n  phase_name text,               -- 'Removal', 'Installation'\n  phase_number int,\n  step_number int,\n  step_name text,                -- matches Executive Checklist\n  tasks_summary text,            -- checklist-level description\n  detail_md text,                -- detailed step content\n  created_at, updated_at\n)\n\n-- NEW: Dependency graph\nsop_dependencies (\n  id uuid PK,\n  from_sop_id uuid FK → sops,\n  to_sop_id uuid FK → sops,\n  link_type text,                -- 'prerequisite'|'sub-procedure'|'optional'|'cross-reference'\n  condition_note text\n)\n\n-- KEEP: Videos (add sop_step_id for step-level mapping)\nsop_recommended_videos (\n  id uuid PK,\n  sop_id uuid FK → sops,\n  sop_step_id uuid FK → sop_steps,  -- NEW: which step this video covers\n  title text,\n  url text,\n  procedure_phase text,\n  sort_order int\n)\n\n-- NEW: AI embeddings\nsop_embeddings (\n  id uuid PK,\n  sop_step_id uuid FK → sop_steps,\n  chunk_text text,\n  embedding vector(1536)\n)\n\n-- KEEP: Audit log\nsop_sync_log (...same...)\n\n-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════\n-- WO ↔ SOP LINKAGE (the bridge)\n-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\n-- Add to existing work_order_templates:\nALTER TABLE work_order_templates\n  ADD COLUMN sop_id uuid REFERENCES sops(id),\n  ADD COLUMN sop_overrides jsonb DEFAULT '{}';  \n  -- overrides = { \"step_3\": { \"detail_md\": \"custom instructions...\" } }\n\n-- Add to existing work_orders:\nALTER TABLE work_orders\n  ADD COLUMN sop_id uuid REFERENCES sops(id);\n\n-- Step-level progress tracking (for timesheets!)\nCREATE TABLE work_order_step_progress (\n  id uuid PK,\n  work_order_id uuid FK → work_orders,\n  sop_step_id uuid FK → sop_steps,\n  status text DEFAULT 'pending',  -- 'pending'|'in_progress'|'completed'|'skipped'\n  completed_by uuid,              -- FK → worker (employee/sub-contractor)\n  completed_at timestamptz,\n  duration_minutes int,           -- employees report this\n  notes text,\n  photo_urls text[],\n  override_detail text,           -- if this WO level customized the step\n  created_at, updated_at\n);\n```\n\n### How the WO Hierarchy Uses SOPs\n\n```\nSystem WO Template (scope='app')\n  └── sop_id = PLB-SOP-001\n  └── sop_overrides = {}  (pure SOP)\n\nCompany WO Template (scope='company', parent=system)\n  └── sop_id = PLB-SOP-001 (inherited)\n  └── sop_overrides = { \"step_2\": { \"detail_md\": \"We use SharkBite fittings\" } }\n\nProject WO Template (scope='project', parent=company)\n  └── sop_id = PLB-SOP-001 (inherited)\n  └── sop_overrides = { \"step_2\": ...(inherited), \"step_5\": { \"not_required\": true } }\n\nUnit WO (actual work order instance)\n  └── sop_id = PLB-SOP-001\n  └── work_order_step_progress rows (one per sop_step)\n      └── Each tracks: status, who completed, duration, notes, photos\n```\n\n### Reconciliation\n\nPeriodic reconciliation becomes a simple query:\n```sql\n-- Find WO templates with overrides that differ from current SOP\nSELECT wot.id, wot.trade_name, wot.scope,\n       wot.sop_overrides,\n       s.revision as current_sop_revision\nFROM work_order_templates wot\nJOIN sops s ON wot.sop_id = s.id\nWHERE wot.sop_overrides != '{}';\n```\n\n### Timesheet Connection\n\n`work_order_step_progress.duration_minutes` is where employee timesheets come from:\n- **Employees**: MUST fill in `duration_minutes` for each step they complete\n- **Sub-contractors (default)**: Only need to set `status = 'completed'`\n- **Sub-contractors (hours required)**: Also fill in `duration_minutes`\n\n---\n\n## Part 3: README.md Update Plan\n\n### Sections to Add\n\n| New Section | Content Source |\n|---|---|\n| **REF Document Management** | sop.md Step 4 — creating/registering trade-level reference docs |\n| **SOP Authoring Workflow** | sop.md Steps 1-7 — the full create/locate lifecycle |\n| **Index Management** | sop.md Steps 2,3,6 — planned→active lifecycle |\n| **Work Order Integration** | Option C design above |\n| **AI/RAG Integration** | sop_embeddings + pgvector semantic search |\n| **Dependency Graph** | sop_dependencies + Mermaid rendering |\n| **Reconciliation** | WO override diffing against current SOP |\n| **Git→DB Sync Pipeline** | GitHub Action: parse → upsert → embed |\n\n### Sections to Update\n\n| Existing Section | Changes |\n|---|---|\n| **Architecture** | Add REF doc layer, git→DB pipeline, WO linkage |\n| **Database Schema** | New 10-table schema (sops, ref_docs, sections, steps, deps, embeddings, videos, sync_log, + WO bridge tables) |\n| **CLI Reference** | Add: `ref create`, `ref list`, `dep show`, `reconcile` commands |\n| **Python API** | Add: ref doc management, dependency queries, embedding generation, reconciliation |\n\n---\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. **📝 Update README.md** — incorporate sop.md workflow + Option C architecture\n2. **🗄️ Schema migration** — new SOP tables + WO linkage columns\n3. **🔧 Update sop_manager.py** — REF doc support, new parser for sections/steps, index management\n4. **🔗 WO template sop_id linkage** — connect existing templates to SOPs\n5. **👷 Workforce tables** — employees/sub-contractors with timesheet rules\n6. **📊 Step progress tracking** — work_order_step_progress for completion + duration\n7. **🤖 Embedding pipeline** — pgvector setup + sync\n8. **🔄 Reconciliation tooling** — diff WO overrides vs current SOP\n\n**What would you like to tackle first?**"
