        "code": "prompt = r\"\"\"# SOP ↔ Work Order Integration — Implementation Prompt\n\n> **Date**: 2026-03-09\n> **Project**: voicelog-scaffold (Hennessy / Team Projects)\n> **Codebase**: `/a0/usr/projects/timesheet_app/voicelog-scaffold`\n> **Stack**: SolidJS frontend, Hono API, Supabase (PostgreSQL), pnpm monorepo\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis prompt implements the bridge between the existing SOP library system and the existing Work Order (WO) template inheritance hierarchy. The goal is to let each WO template reference an SOP, expose SOP steps through the WO API, and track step-level completion/duration at the unit work order level — feeding a separate timesheet application.\n\nThe design principle is **surgical integration**: we add to existing files rather than creating parallel structures. The existing WO inheritance chain (system → company → project → unit) stays untouched. SOP linkage rides along automatically through the existing copy/freeze mechanisms.\n\n---\n\n## Context: What Already Exists\n\n### WO Template Inheritance (DO NOT MODIFY)\n\nThe three-tier template hierarchy is fully implemented:\n\n```\nSystem WO Template (scope='system', org=NULL, project=NULL)\n  └── copied to → Company WO Template (scope='company', org=X, project=NULL)\n      └── lazy-ref → Project WO Template (scope='project', org=X, project=Y)\n          └── (frozen when project activates)\n```\n\n**Key files** (read these first to understand the patterns):\n\n| File | Lines | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `supabase/migrations/20260222000002_project_lifecycle_template_inheritance.sql` | 95 | `is_frozen`, NULL definition lazy-copy, `freeze_project_templates()` trigger |\n| `apps/api/src/routes/work-orders.ts` | 1121 | 3 inheritance endpoints: `assign-to-company`, `assign-to-project`, `GET project/:projectId` with parent resolution |\n| `apps/api/src/routes/onboard.ts` | 415 | `copyTemplatesToOrg()` — copies system→company templates during onboarding |\n| `apps/work-orders/src/lib/api.ts` | 746 | `WorkOrderTemplate` interface, `getTemplates(scope?)` method |\n| `apps/work-orders/src/pages/ProjectTemplates.tsx` | 274 | Frozen/inherited badges |\n| `apps/work-orders/src/pages/TemplateDetail.tsx` | 219 | Parent/copied-from links |\n| `apps/work-orders/src/pages/TemplateEditor.tsx` | 531 | Frozen template warning |\n\n**Key columns on `work_order_templates`** (already exist, some unused):\n```sql\nscope           TEXT     -- 'system' | 'company' | 'project'\nparent_template_id  UUID -- company→project link (lazy-copy parent)\ncopied_from_template_id UUID -- tracks origin\nsource_template_id  UUID -- added in phase1, UNUSED\nsop_id          UUID     -- FK → sops, added in phase1, UNUSED ← WE WILL USE THIS\ntrade_id        UUID     -- FK → trades, added in phase1\ninheritance_depth INT    -- added in phase1, UNUSED\nis_frozen       BOOLEAN  -- set when project activates\ndefinition      JSONB    -- NULL = lazy-copy from parent\n```\n\n### SOP Library (EXISTS but disconnected from WO flow)\n\n**Migration**: `supabase/migrations/20260228000001_sop_library.sql`\n\nExisting tables:\n```sql\nsops                      -- master index (sop_number, trade_code, trade_name, task_name, status, etc.)\nsop_executive_checklists  -- cached checklist items (sop_id, phase_name, step_number, step_name, tasks)\nsop_detailed_steps        -- cached detailed steps (sop_id, phase_name, step_number, detail_markdown)\nsop_recommended_videos    -- video links per SOP\nsop_sync_log              -- git→DB sync audit trail\n```\n\n**Phase 1 additions** (`20260304000001_schema_evolution_phase1.sql`):\n```sql\nsops.trade_id   UUID  -- FK → trades (exists)\nsops.scope      TEXT  -- 'system' default (exists)\nsops.outcome_id UUID  -- FK → project_outcomes (exists)\n```\n\n### SOP Authoring Workflow (docs-as-code)\n\nSOPs are authored as markdown files following SOP-META-001 Rev 1.3:\n- Location: `docs/sop/{TRADE}/SOP_{TRADE}_{Task_Name}.md`\n- REF docs: `docs/sop/{TRADE}/REF_{TRADE}_Codes_Standards.md` (shared per trade)\n- Index: `docs/sop/SOP_INDEX.md` (master registry)\n- Each SOP has: Executive Checklists (max 7 steps per phase) + Detailed Steps\n- Phases are logical groupings: Removal, Installation, Prep, Apply, Finish, etc.\n\n### Timesheet App (SEPARATE — do not build)\n\nA separate application consumes `work_order_step_progress` data to build employee timesheets. We only need to provide the tracking table and API endpoints. The timesheet app will overlay duration data from step progress records.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Conversation 1: Database Migration\n\nCreate ONE new migration file:\n```\nsupabase/migrations/20260310000001_sop_wo_bridge.sql\n```\n\n#### 1A. Create `sop_sections` table\n\nReplaces the flat `sop_executive_checklists` + `sop_detailed_steps` with a unified, hierarchical structure that supports both RAG chunking and WO step tracking.\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.sop_sections (\n    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    sop_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sops(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    section_number INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    section_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (section_type IN (\n        'purpose', 'scope', 'references', 'personnel', 'safety',\n        'tools', 'pre_work', 'procedure', 'videos', 'testing',\n        'cleanup', 'troubleshooting', 'quality', 'revision_history'\n    )),\n    title TEXT NOT NULL,\n    content_md TEXT,              -- full markdown content\n    content_plain TEXT,           -- stripped text for tsvector search\n    is_ref_pointer BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,  -- true if \"See REF doc\"\n    ref_section TEXT,             -- which REF section it points to\n    phase_name TEXT,              -- only for section_type='procedure': 'Removal', 'Installation'\n    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    UNIQUE(sop_id, section_number)\n);\n\nCOMMENT ON TABLE public.sop_sections IS 'Structured sections parsed from SOP markdown files';\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_sections_sop ON public.sop_sections(sop_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_sections_type ON public.sop_sections(section_type);\n```\n\n#### 1B. Create `sop_steps` table\n\nEach row = one trackable unit of work = one RAG chunk. This is the table that `work_order_step_progress` references.\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.sop_steps (\n    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    sop_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sops(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    section_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sop_sections(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    phase_name TEXT NOT NULL,         -- 'Removal', 'Installation'\n    phase_number INTEGER NOT NULL,    -- matches section_number\n    step_number INTEGER NOT NULL,     -- 1-7 per phase (Executive Checklist rule)\n    step_name TEXT NOT NULL,          -- matches Executive Checklist AND Detailed Steps heading\n    tasks_summary TEXT,               -- brief description from Executive Checklist\n    detail_md TEXT,                   -- full detailed step content (markdown)\n    detail_plain TEXT,                -- stripped text for search\n    est_duration_minutes INTEGER,     -- estimated time for this step\n    requires_photo BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\n    requires_measurement BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\n    sort_order INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    UNIQUE(sop_id, phase_number, step_number)\n);\n\nCOMMENT ON TABLE public.sop_steps IS 'Individual trackable steps parsed from SOP procedure phases. One row = one checklist item = one RAG chunk.';\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_steps_sop ON public.sop_steps(sop_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_steps_section ON public.sop_steps(section_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_steps_phase ON public.sop_steps(sop_id, phase_number);\n```\n\n#### 1C. Create `sop_dependencies` table\n\nGraph of prerequisite/sub-procedure relationships between SOPs.\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.sop_dependencies (\n    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    from_sop_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sops(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    to_sop_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sops(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    link_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (link_type IN (\n        'prerequisite', 'sub_procedure', 'cross_reference', 'optional'\n    )),\n    condition_note TEXT,           -- when/why this dependency applies\n    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    UNIQUE(from_sop_id, to_sop_id, link_type)\n);\n\nCOMMENT ON TABLE public.sop_dependencies IS 'Directed graph of SOP relationships: prerequisites, sub-procedures, cross-references';\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_deps_from ON public.sop_dependencies(from_sop_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_sop_deps_to ON public.sop_dependencies(to_sop_id);\n```\n\n#### 1D. Create `work_order_step_progress` table\n\nThis is the bridge table where field workers record completion of each SOP step within a unit work order. The separate timesheet app reads this data.\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.work_order_step_progress (\n    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    work_order_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.work_orders(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    sop_step_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.sop_steps(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT,\n    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN (\n        'pending', 'in_progress', 'completed', 'skipped', 'blocked'\n    )),\n    completed_by UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),\n    started_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\n    completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\n    duration_minutes INTEGER,         -- actual time spent (employees MUST fill; subs optional)\n    notes TEXT,\n    photo_urls TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',\n    override_detail TEXT,             -- if this WO level customized the step instructions\n    is_override BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\n    organization_id UUID REFERENCES public.organizations(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    UNIQUE(work_order_id, sop_step_id)\n);\n\nCOMMENT ON TABLE public.work_order_step_progress IS 'Step-level completion tracking for unit work orders. Each row tracks one SOP step within one WO. Duration feeds timesheet app.';\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_wo_step_progress_wo ON public.work_order_step_progress(work_order_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_wo_step_progress_step ON public.work_order_step_progress(sop_step_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_wo_step_progress_user ON public.work_order_step_progress(completed_by);\nCREATE INDEX idx_wo_step_progress_status ON public.work_order_step_progress(status);\nCREATE INDEX idx_wo_step_progress_org ON public.work_order_step_progress(organization_id);\n```\n\n#### 1E. Create `sop_ref_docs` table\n\nTrade-level reference documents that SOPs point to instead of duplicating shared content.\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.sop_ref_docs (\n    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    doc_id TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,       -- 'REF-PLB-001'\n    trade_code TEXT NOT NULL,\n    trade_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n    trade_id UUID REFERENCES public.trades(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,\n    revision TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '1.0',\n    content_md TEXT,                    -- full markdown content\n    storage_path TEXT,                  -- path in storage bucket\n    file_hash TEXT,                     -- MD5 for change detection\n    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCOMMENT ON TABLE public.sop_ref_docs IS 'Trade-level reference documents (codes, standards, PPE, personnel) that SOPs link to via pointers';\n```\n\n#### 1F. Add `ref_doc_id` to `sops` table\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE public.sops\n    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS ref_doc_id UUID REFERENCES public.sop_ref_docs(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;\n```\n\n#### 1G. Add `sop_step_id` to `sop_recommended_videos`\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE public.sop_recommended_videos\n    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS sop_step_id UUID REFERENCES public.sop_steps(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;\n```\n\n#### 1H. Update `freeze_project_templates()` trigger\n\nEnsure `sop_id` is preserved when freezing project templates:\n\n```sql\nCREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.freeze_project_templates()\nRETURNS TRIGGER AS $$\nBEGIN\n  IF NEW.status = 'active' AND (OLD.status IS DISTINCT FROM 'active') THEN\n    UPDATE public.work_order_templates pt\n    SET\n      definition = ct.definition,\n      sop_id = COALESCE(pt.sop_id, ct.sop_id),  -- inherit sop_id if not already set\n      is_frozen = true,\n      updated_at = now()\n    FROM public.work_order_templates ct\n    WHERE pt.project_id = NEW.id\n      AND pt.scope = 'project'\n      AND pt.parent_template_id = ct.id\n      AND pt.is_frozen = false\n      AND pt.definition IS NULL;\n  END IF;\n  RETURN NEW;\nEND;\n$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;\n```\n\n#### 1I. RLS Policies\n\n```sql\n-- sop_sections: readable by all authenticated\nALTER TABLE public.sop_sections ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_sections_select\" ON public.sop_sections FOR SELECT\n    USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_sections_sysadmin\" ON public.sop_sections FOR ALL\n    USING (public.is_sysadmin());\n\n-- sop_steps: readable by all authenticated\nALTER TABLE public.sop_steps ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_steps_select\" ON public.sop_steps FOR SELECT\n    USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_steps_sysadmin\" ON public.sop_steps FOR ALL\n    USING (public.is_sysadmin());\n\n-- sop_dependencies: readable by all authenticated\nALTER TABLE public.sop_dependencies ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_deps_select\" ON public.sop_dependencies FOR SELECT\n    USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_deps_sysadmin\" ON public.sop_dependencies FOR ALL\n    USING (public.is_sysadmin());\n\n-- sop_ref_docs: readable by all authenticated\nALTER TABLE public.sop_ref_docs ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_ref_docs_select\" ON public.sop_ref_docs FOR SELECT\n    USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');\nCREATE POLICY \"sop_ref_docs_sysadmin\" ON public.sop_ref_docs FOR ALL\n    USING (public.is_sysadmin());\n\n-- work_order_step_progress: tenant isolation\nALTER TABLE public.work_order_step_progress ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nCREATE POLICY \"wo_step_progress_tenant\" ON public.work_order_step_progress FOR ALL\n    USING (organization_id = public.current_user_organization_id());\nCREATE POLICY \"wo_step_progress_sysadmin\" ON public.work_order_step_progress FOR ALL\n    USING (public.is_sysadmin());\n```\n\n#### 1J. Updated timestamp triggers\n\n```sql\nCREATE TRIGGER update_sop_sections_updated_at\n    BEFORE UPDATE ON public.sop_sections\n    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();\n\nCREATE TRIGGER update_sop_steps_updated_at\n    BEFORE UPDATE ON public.sop_steps\n    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();\n\nCREATE TRIGGER update_sop_ref_docs_updated_at\n    BEFORE UPDATE ON public.sop_ref_docs\n    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();\n\nCREATE TRIGGER update_wo_step_progress_updated_at\n    BEFORE UPDATE ON public.work_order_step_progress\n    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();\n```\n\n#### Verification\n\nAfter applying the migration, verify:\n```sql\n-- All new tables exist\nSELECT table_name FROM information_schema.tables\nWHERE table_schema = 'public'\nAND table_name IN ('sop_sections', 'sop_steps', 'sop_dependencies', 'work_order_step_progress', 'sop_ref_docs');\n\n-- sop_id column exists on work_order_templates (should already exist)\nSELECT column_name FROM information_schema.columns\nWHERE table_name = 'work_order_templates' AND column_name = 'sop_id';\n\n-- freeze trigger updated\nSELECT prosrc FROM pg_proc WHERE proname = 'freeze_project_templates';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Conversation 2: API Layer\n\nEdit ONE existing file: `apps/api/src/routes/work-orders.ts`\n\nAdd these endpoints (insert after the existing template endpoints, before the work order CRUD section):\n\n#### 2A. GET `/templates/:id/sop` — Get linked SOP with steps\n\nReturns the SOP linked to a template, including all sections and steps. For project-scope templates, resolves `sop_id` from parent if not set locally.\n\n```typescript\n// GET SOP linked to a template (with inheritance resolution)\nworkOrdersRoute.get('/templates/:id/sop', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const id = c.req.param('id');\n\n    // Get template\n    const { data: template, error: tErr } = await supabase\n        .from('work_order_templates')\n        .select('id, sop_id, parent_template_id, scope')\n        .eq('id', id)\n        .single();\n\n    if (tErr || !template) return c.json({ error: 'Template not found' }, 404);\n\n    // Resolve sop_id: local → parent → null\n    let sopId = template.sop_id;\n    if (!sopId && template.parent_template_id) {\n        const { data: parent } = await supabase\n            .from('work_order_templates')\n            .select('sop_id')\n            .eq('id', template.parent_template_id)\n            .single();\n        sopId = parent?.sop_id;\n    }\n\n    if (!sopId) return c.json({ sop: null, steps: [], sections: [] });\n\n    // Fetch SOP with sections and steps\n    const [sopRes, sectionsRes, stepsRes] = await Promise.all([\n        supabase.from('sops').select('*').eq('id', sopId).single(),\n        supabase.from('sop_sections').select('*').eq('sop_id', sopId).order('section_number'),\n        supabase.from('sop_steps').select('*').eq('sop_id', sopId).order('phase_number').order('step_number'),\n    ]);\n\n    return c.json({\n        sop: sopRes.data,\n        sections: sectionsRes.data || [],\n        steps: stepsRes.data || [],\n        _inherited: sopId !== template.sop_id,\n    });\n});\n```\n\n#### 2B. GET `/work-orders/:id/step-progress` — Get step progress for a WO\n\nReturns all step progress records for a work order, joined with SOP step details.\n\n```typescript\n// GET step progress for a work order\nworkOrdersRoute.get('/work-orders/:id/step-progress', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const woId = c.req.param('id');\n\n    const { data, error } = await supabase\n        .from('work_order_step_progress')\n        .select(`\n            *,\n            sop_step:sop_steps (\n                id, phase_name, phase_number, step_number, step_name,\n                tasks_summary, detail_md, est_duration_minutes\n            )\n        `)\n        .eq('work_order_id', woId)\n        .order('created_at');\n\n    if (error) return c.json({ error: error.message }, 500);\n    return c.json(data || []);\n});\n```\n\n#### 2C. POST `/work-orders/:id/initialize-steps` — Create step progress records\n\nWhen a work order is started, create `work_order_step_progress` rows for each SOP step. This is called once when a WO transitions from created to in-progress.\n\n```typescript\n// Initialize step progress records for a work order from its template's SOP\nworkOrdersRoute.post('/work-orders/:id/initialize-steps', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const woId = c.req.param('id');\n\n    // Get the work order and its template's sop_id\n    const { data: wo, error: woErr } = await supabase\n        .from('work_orders')\n        .select('id, template_id, organization_id, work_order_templates!inner(sop_id, parent_template_id)')\n        .eq('id', woId)\n        .single();\n\n    if (woErr || !wo) return c.json({ error: 'Work order not found' }, 404);\n\n    // Resolve sop_id (same inheritance logic)\n    let sopId = (wo as any).work_order_templates?.sop_id;\n    if (!sopId && (wo as any).work_order_templates?.parent_template_id) {\n        const { data: parent } = await supabase\n            .from('work_order_templates')\n            .select('sop_id')\n            .eq('id', (wo as any).work_order_templates.parent_template_id)\n            .single();\n        sopId = parent?.sop_id;\n    }\n\n    if (!sopId) return c.json({ error: 'No SOP linked to this work order template' }, 400);\n\n    // Get all SOP steps\n    const { data: steps, error: stepsErr } = await supabase\n        .from('sop_steps')\n        .select('id')\n        .eq('sop_id', sopId)\n        .order('phase_number')\n        .order('step_number');\n\n    if (stepsErr || !steps?.length) return c.json({ error: 'No SOP steps found' }, 400);\n\n    // Check if already initialized\n    const { count } = await supabase\n        .from('work_order_step_progress')\n        .select('id', { count: 'exact', head: true })\n        .eq('work_order_id', woId);\n\n    if (count && count > 0) return c.json({ error: 'Steps already initialized', count }, 409);\n\n    // Create progress records\n    const records = steps.map(step => ({\n        work_order_id: woId,\n        sop_step_id: step.id,\n        status: 'pending',\n        organization_id: wo.organization_id,\n    }));\n\n    const { data: created, error: insertErr } = await supabase\n        .from('work_order_step_progress')\n        .insert(records)\n        .select();\n\n    if (insertErr) return c.json({ error: insertErr.message }, 500);\n    return c.json({ initialized: created?.length || 0 }, 201);\n});\n```\n\n#### 2D. PATCH `/work-orders/step-progress/:id` — Update step progress\n\nField workers update individual step progress (status, duration, notes, photos).\n\n```typescript\n// Update a step progress record\nworkOrdersRoute.patch('/work-orders/step-progress/:id', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const id = c.req.param('id');\n    const body = await c.req.json();\n\n    const allowedFields = [\n        'status', 'completed_by', 'started_at', 'completed_at',\n        'duration_minutes', 'notes', 'photo_urls', 'override_detail', 'is_override'\n    ];\n\n    const updates: Record<string, any> = {};\n    for (const field of allowedFields) {\n        if (body[field] !== undefined) updates[field] = body[field];\n    }\n\n    // Auto-set timestamps based on status\n    if (updates.status === 'in_progress' && !updates.started_at) {\n        updates.started_at = new Date().toISOString();\n    }\n    if (updates.status === 'completed' && !updates.completed_at) {\n        updates.completed_at = new Date().toISOString();\n    }\n\n    const { data, error } = await supabase\n        .from('work_order_step_progress')\n        .update(updates)\n        .eq('id', id)\n        .select()\n        .single();\n\n    if (error) return c.json({ error: error.message }, 500);\n    return c.json(data);\n});\n```\n\n#### 2E. GET `/sops` and GET `/sops/:id` — SOP listing and detail\n\nAdd to work-orders.ts OR create a new `sops.ts` route file (prefer adding to work-orders.ts to avoid clutter):\n\n```typescript\n// List SOPs (optionally filtered by trade)\nworkOrdersRoute.get('/sops', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const tradeId = c.req.query('trade_id');\n    const tradeCode = c.req.query('trade_code');\n\n    let query = supabase\n        .from('sops')\n        .select('id, sop_number, trade_code, trade_name, task_name, revision, status, estimated_duration, trade_id')\n        .eq('status', 'active')\n        .order('trade_code')\n        .order('sop_number');\n\n    if (tradeId) query = query.eq('trade_id', tradeId);\n    if (tradeCode) query = query.eq('trade_code', tradeCode);\n\n    const { data, error } = await query;\n    if (error) return c.json({ error: error.message }, 500);\n    return c.json(data || []);\n});\n\n// Get SOP detail with sections and steps\nworkOrdersRoute.get('/sops/:id', async (c) => {\n    const supabase = getScopedClient(c);\n    const id = c.req.param('id');\n\n    const [sopRes, sectionsRes, stepsRes, depsRes] = await Promise.all([\n        supabase.from('sops').select('*').eq('id', id).single(),\n        supabase.from('sop_sections').select('*').eq('sop_id', id).order('section_number'),\n        supabase.from('sop_steps').select('*').eq('sop_id', id).order('phase_number').order('step_number'),\n        supabase.from('sop_dependencies').select('*, to_sop:sops!to_sop_id(sop_number, task_name)').eq('from_sop_id', id),\n    ]);\n\n    if (sopRes.error) return c.json({ error: sopRes.error.message }, 404);\n\n    return c.json({\n        ...sopRes.data,\n        sections: sectionsRes.data || [],\n        steps: stepsRes.data || [],\n        dependencies: depsRes.data || [],\n    });\n});\n```\n\n#### 2F. PATCH `/templates/:id` — Add sop_id to allowed update fields\n\nIn the existing PATCH endpoint for templates, add `sop_id` to the `allowedFields` array (line ~389):\n\n```typescript\n// EXISTING LINE ~389:\nconst allowedFields = ['trade_name', 'trade_id', 'definition', 'version', 'is_active', 'scope', 'project_id', 'library_id', 'outcome_id'];\n// CHANGE TO:\nconst allowedFields = ['trade_name', 'trade_id', 'definition', 'version', 'is_active', 'scope', 'project_id', 'library_id', 'outcome_id', 'sop_id'];\n```\n\n---\n\n### Conversation 3: Frontend Updates\n\nEdit existing files only — no new pages.\n\n#### 3A. `apps/work-orders/src/lib/api.ts` — Add types and methods\n\nAdd these interfaces after the existing `WorkOrderTemplate` interface:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SopSummary {\n    id: string;\n    sop_number: string;\n    trade_code: string;\n    trade_name: string;\n    task_name: string;\n    revision: string;\n    status: string;\n    estimated_duration?: string;\n    trade_id?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface SopSection {\n    id: string;\n    sop_id: string;\n    section_number: number;\n    section_type: string;\n    title: string;\n    content_md?: string;\n    phase_name?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface SopStep {\n    id: string;\n    sop_id: string;\n    section_id: string;\n    phase_name: string;\n    phase_number: number;\n    step_number: number;\n    step_name: string;\n    tasks_summary?: string;\n    detail_md?: string;\n    est_duration_minutes?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface StepProgress {\n    id: string;\n    work_order_id: string;\n    sop_step_id: string;\n    status: 'pending' | 'in_progress' | 'completed' | 'skipped' | 'blocked';\n    completed_by?: string;\n    started_at?: string;\n    completed_at?: string;\n    duration_minutes?: number;\n    notes?: string;\n    photo_urls?: string[];\n    override_detail?: string;\n    is_override?: boolean;\n    sop_step?: SopStep;  // joined from API\n}\n```\n\nAdd these methods to the `WorkOrdersAPI` class:\n\n```typescript\n// SOP methods\nasync getSops(tradeCode?: string): Promise<SopSummary[]> {\n    const query = tradeCode ? `?trade_code=${tradeCode}` : '';\n    return this.request<SopSummary[]>(`/sops${query}`);\n}\n\nasync getSop(id: string): Promise<any> {\n    return this.request<any>(`/sops/${id}`);\n}\n\nasync getTemplateSop(templateId: string): Promise<{ sop: SopSummary | null; steps: SopStep[]; sections: SopSection[]; _inherited: boolean }> {\n    return this.request(`/templates/${templateId}/sop`);\n}\n\n// Step progress methods\nasync getStepProgress(workOrderId: string): Promise<StepProgress[]> {\n    return this.request<StepProgress[]>(`/work-orders/${workOrderId}/step-progress`);\n}\n\nasync initializeSteps(workOrderId: string): Promise<{ initialized: number }> {\n    return this.request(`/work-orders/${workOrderId}/initialize-steps`, { method: 'POST' });\n}\n\nasync updateStepProgress(progressId: string, updates: Partial<StepProgress>): Promise<StepProgress> {\n    return this.request(`/work-orders/step-progress/${progressId}`, {\n        method: 'PATCH',\n        body: JSON.stringify(updates),\n    });\n}\n```\n\n#### 3B. `apps/work-orders/src/pages/TemplateDetail.tsx` — Show linked SOP\n\nAdd an SOP info section after the existing metadata display (after the parent_template_id Show block around line 115):\n\n```tsx\n<Show when={template()!.sop_id}>\n    <div class=\"mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg border border-blue-200\">\n        <p class=\"text-sm font-medium text-blue-800 uppercase mb-2\">Linked SOP</p>\n        {/* Fetch and display SOP summary */}\n        <SopLink sopId={template()!.sop_id!} />\n    </div>\n</Show>\n```\n\nCreate a small `SopLink` component (can be inline in the same file):\n\n```tsx\nfunction SopLink(props: { sopId: string }) {\n    const [sop] = createResource(() => props.sopId, async (id) => {\n        const res = await api.getSop(id);\n        return res;\n    });\n\n    return (\n        <Show when={sop()} fallback={<span class=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">Loading...</span>}>\n            <div class=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n                <span class=\"font-mono text-sm font-bold text-blue-700\">{sop()!.sop_number}</span>\n                <span class=\"text-sm text-gray-700\">{sop()!.task_name}</span>\n                <span class=\"text-xs text-gray-500\">Rev {sop()!.revision}</span>\n            </div>\n        </Show>\n    );\n}\n```\n\n#### 3C. `apps/work-orders/src/pages/WorkOrderDetail.tsx` — Step progress display\n\nAdd a \"Procedure Steps\" section to the work order detail page showing step progress with status toggles. This is the primary UI for field workers.\n\n```tsx\n// Add a StepProgressPanel component\nfunction StepProgressPanel(props: { workOrderId: string }) {\n    const [progress, { refetch }] = createResource(\n        () => props.workOrderId,\n        (id) => api.getStepProgress(id)\n    );\n\n    const initSteps = async () => {\n        await api.initializeSteps(props.workOrderId);\n        refetch();\n    };\n\n    const updateStep = async (progressId: string, status: string) => {\n        await api.updateStepProgress(progressId, { status } as any);\n        refetch();\n    };\n\n    return (\n        <div class=\"mt-6\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-lg font-semibold mb-4\">Procedure Steps</h3>\n            <Show when={progress()?.length} fallback={\n                <button onClick={initSteps} class=\"btn btn-primary\">\n                    Initialize Steps from SOP\n                </button>\n            }>\n                <div class=\"space-y-2\">\n                    <For each={progress()!}>\n                        {(step) => (\n                            <div class={`flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded border ${\n                                step.status === 'completed' ? 'bg-green-50 border-green-200' :\n                                step.status === 'in_progress' ? 'bg-yellow-50 border-yellow-200' :\n                                'bg-white border-gray-200'\n                            }`}>\n                                <select\n                                    value={step.status}\n                                    onChange={(e) => updateStep(step.id, e.target.value)}\n                                    class=\"text-sm border rounded px-2 py-1\"\n                                >\n                                    <option value=\"pending\">⬜ Pending</option>\n                                    <option value=\"in_progress\">🔶 In Progress</option>\n                                    <option value=\"completed\">✅ Completed</option>\n                                    <option value=\"skipped\">⏭️ Skipped</option>\n                                    <option value=\"blocked\">🚫 Blocked</option>\n                                </select>\n                                <div class=\"flex-1\">\n                                    <span class=\"font-medium text-sm\">\n                                        {step.sop_step?.phase_name} — Step {step.sop_step?.step_number}: {step.sop_step?.step_name}\n                                    </span>\n                                    <Show when={step.sop_step?.tasks_summary}>\n                                        <p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1\">{step.sop_step!.tasks_summary}</p>\n                                    </Show>\n                             