        "code": "cat > /a0/usr/projects/timesheet_app/voicelog-scaffold/docs/workorders/SOP_WO_WORKFLOW.md << 'ENDOFFILE'\n# SOP ↔ Work Order Integration — Workflow & Logic\n\n> **Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n> **Status**: Post-implementation reference document\n> **Audience**: Developers, system administrators, and the timesheet application team\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [System Overview](#1-system-overview)\n2. [Data Model](#2-data-model)\n3. [SOP Authoring & Ingestion](#3-sop-authoring--ingestion)\n4. [WO Template Inheritance Chain](#4-wo-template-inheritance-chain)\n5. [SOP ↔ WO Template Linkage](#5-sop--wo-template-linkage)\n6. [Unit Work Order Lifecycle](#6-unit-work-order-lifecycle)\n7. [Step Progress Tracking](#7-step-progress-tracking)\n8. [Timesheet App Integration](#8-timesheet-app-integration)\n9. [API Reference](#9-api-reference)\n10. [Frontend Surfaces](#10-frontend-surfaces)\n11. [Edge Cases & Business Rules](#11-edge-cases--business-rules)\n\n---\n\n## 1. System Overview\n\nThe system connects three domains:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│  SOP Library    │────▶│  Work Order System   │────▶│  Timesheet App  │\n│  (Knowledge)    │     │  (Execution)         │     │  (Reporting)    │\n└─────────────────┘     └──────────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n     Markdown               Templates + WOs            Duration data\n     docs-as-code           3-tier inheritance          per employee\n     Git-managed            Step-level tracking         per step\n```\n\n**Core principle**: SOPs are the single source of truth for *how* work is done. Work orders are the execution layer that tracks *who* did *what* and *how long* it took. The timesheet app consumes duration data to produce payroll-ready reports.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Model\n\n### Entity Relationship Overview\n\n```\nsop_ref_docs (1 per trade)\n    │\n    ▼\nsops (master index)\n    │\n    ├──▶ sop_sections (structured content)\n    │       │\n    │       └──▶ sop_steps (trackable units of work)\n    │               │\n    │               └──▶ work_order_step_progress (completion tracking)\n    │                       │\n    │                       └──▶ [Timesheet App reads this]\n    │\n    ├──▶ sop_dependencies (prerequisite graph)\n    │\n    └──▶ sop_recommended_videos (training links)\n\nwork_order_templates (3-tier hierarchy)\n    │\n    ├── scope='system'  ──(sop_id)──▶ sops\n    │       │\n    │       └── copied to ──▶ scope='company'  ──(sop_id inherited)──▶ sops\n    │                               │\n    │                               └── lazy-ref ──▶ scope='project'  ──(sop_id inherited)──▶ sops\n    │\n    └──▶ work_orders (unit instances)\n            │\n            └──▶ work_order_step_progress\n```\n\n### Key Tables\n\n| Table | Purpose | Row Count Pattern |\n|---|---|---|\n| `sops` | Master SOP index | ~50-200 (one per trade task) |\n| `sop_sections` | Structured content blocks | ~10-15 per SOP |\n| `sop_steps` | Trackable work units | ~5-30 per SOP (max 7 per phase) |\n| `sop_ref_docs` | Shared trade reference docs | 1 per trade |\n| `sop_dependencies` | SOP prerequisite graph | Sparse |\n| `work_order_templates` | 3-tier template hierarchy | ~8 per scope tier |\n| `work_orders` | Unit work instances | Grows with projects |\n| `work_order_step_progress` | Step completion + duration | N steps × M work orders |\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOP Authoring & Ingestion\n\n### 3.1 Authoring (docs-as-code)\n\nSOPs are authored as markdown files following the SOP-META-001 Rev 1.3 format:\n\n```\ndocs/sop/\n├── SOP_INDEX.md                          # Master registry\n├── SOP_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md                # Format specification\n├── SOP_TEMPLATE.md                       # Blank template\n├── PNT/                                  # Trade: Painting\n│   ├── REF_PNT_Codes_Standards.md        # Shared reference doc\n│   ├── SOP_PNT_Interior_Painting.md      # Task-specific SOP\n│   └── SOP_PNT_Exterior_Painting.md\n├── PLB/                                  # Trade: Plumbing\n│   └── SOP_PLB_Rough_In.md\n└── ELC/                                  # Trade: Electrical\n    └── SOP_ELC_Rough_In.md\n```\n\nEach SOP contains up to 15 standardized sections:\n1. Purpose\n2. Scope (with dependency references)\n3. References / Applicable Codes\n4. Personnel Qualifications\n5. Safety / PPE Requirements\n6. Tools & Equipment\n7. Pre-Work Checklist\n8. **Procedure** (multiple phases, each with Executive Checklist + Detailed Steps)\n9. Recommended Training Videos\n10. Testing & Verification\n11. Cleanup & Waste Disposal\n12. Troubleshooting\n13. Quality Assurance\n14. Revision History\n\n### 3.2 REF Documents\n\nTrade-level reference documents (`REF_{TRADE}_Codes_Standards.md`) contain shared content that multiple SOPs within the same trade reference. This eliminates duplication — SOPs point to REF sections instead of repeating codes, PPE lists, and personnel requirements.\n\n```\nSOP says: \"See REF-PNT-001, Section 3: Applicable Codes\"\n    │\n    └──▶ sop_sections row with is_ref_pointer=true, ref_section='3'\n              │\n              └──▶ sop_ref_docs row with doc_id='REF-PNT-001'\n```\n\n### 3.3 Ingestion Pipeline (sop_manager.py)\n\nThe SOP Manager skill (`skills/sop_library_manager/`) syncs markdown files into the database:\n\n```\nMarkdown File\n    │\n    ▼\nparse_to_sections_and_steps()\n    │\n    ├──▶ sop_sections[]     (structured content blocks)\n    ├──▶ sop_steps[]         (trackable work units from Executive Checklists)\n    └──▶ sop_dependencies[]  (parsed from Scope section cross-references)\n    │\n    ▼\nsync_sop_to_new_schema()\n    │\n    ├──▶ DELETE existing sections/steps for this SOP\n    ├──▶ INSERT new sections\n    ├──▶ INSERT new steps\n    └──▶ UPSERT dependencies\n    │\n    ▼\nsop_sync_log (audit trail)\n```\n\n**Step extraction logic**: The parser reads Executive Checklist tables from procedure phases. Each table row becomes one `sop_steps` record. The step name is cross-referenced with the Detailed Steps section to attach the full `detail_md` content.\n\n```markdown\n## 8. Procedure — Phase 1: Surface Preparation\n\n### Executive Checklist\n| Step | Task | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| 1 | Inspect Surfaces | Check for damage, moisture, previous coatings |\n| 2 | Clean Surfaces | Remove dust, grease, mildew per SSPC-SP1 |\n| 3 | Repair Defects | Fill holes, caulk gaps, sand rough areas |\n\n### Detailed Steps\n#### Step 1: Inspect Surfaces\nUsing a moisture meter, check all surfaces...\n```\n\nBecomes:\n```\nsop_sections: { section_number: 8, section_type: 'procedure', phase_name: 'Surface Preparation' }\nsop_steps:    { phase_number: 1, step_number: 1, step_name: 'Inspect Surfaces', tasks_summary: 'Check for damage...', detail_md: 'Using a moisture meter...' }\nsop_steps:    { phase_number: 1, step_number: 2, step_name: 'Clean Surfaces', ... }\nsop_steps:    { phase_number: 1, step_number: 3, step_name: 'Repair Defects', ... }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. WO Template Inheritance Chain\n\n### 4.1 Three-Tier Hierarchy\n\nWork order templates exist at three scope levels. Each level inherits from the one above:\n\n```\nTier 1: SYSTEM templates (scope='system', org=NULL, project=NULL)\n│   Created by sysadmin. Represent canonical trade definitions.\n│   Linked to SOPs via sop_id column.\n│\n├── Tier 2: COMPANY templates (scope='company', org=X, project=NULL)\n│   │   Created during tenant onboarding via copyTemplatesToOrg().\n│   │   Full copy of system template including sop_id.\n│   │   Company can customize definition without affecting system template.\n│   │\n│   └── Tier 3: PROJECT templates (scope='project', org=X, project=Y)\n│           Created when templates are assigned to a project.\n│           Uses LAZY-COPY: definition=NULL means \"use parent's definition\".\n│           Frozen when project status changes to 'active'.\n│           sop_id inherited from company template (or overridden locally).\n```\n\n### 4.2 Copy Mechanisms\n\n**System → Company** (during onboarding):\n```\ncopyTemplatesToOrg(orgId) in onboard.ts:\n  1. SELECT all system-scope templates\n  2. For each: INSERT new company-scope template with:\n     - copied_from_template_id = system template id\n     - sop_id = system template's sop_id  ← SOP link preserved\n     - definition = system template's definition (full copy)\n     - scope = 'company'\n     - organization_id = new org id\n```\n\n**Company → Project** (template assignment):\n```\nassign-to-project endpoint in work-orders.ts:\n  1. INSERT project-scope template with:\n     - parent_template_id = company template id\n     - sop_id = NULL (inherits from parent via lazy resolution)\n     - definition = NULL (lazy-copy: resolved at read time)\n     - scope = 'project'\n     - is_frozen = false\n```\n\n**Freeze on project activation**:\n```\nfreeze_project_templates() trigger:\n  When project.status changes to 'active':\n  1. For each unfrozen project template with NULL definition:\n     - Copy definition from parent (company) template\n     - Copy sop_id from parent if not set locally\n     - Set is_frozen = true\n  2. Template is now immutable for the project's lifetime\n```\n\n### 4.3 SOP Resolution Through Inheritance\n\nWhen reading a template's SOP, the system resolves through the chain:\n\n```\nGET /templates/:id/sop\n  1. Read template.sop_id\n  2. If NULL and template has parent_template_id:\n     → Read parent.sop_id\n  3. If still NULL: return { sop: null }\n  4. If found: fetch SOP with sections and steps\n  5. Response includes _inherited: true/false flag\n```\n\nThis means a project template automatically gets its SOP from the company template without any explicit copying.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SOP ↔ WO Template Linkage\n\n### 5.1 How Templates Get Linked to SOPs\n\nThere are two paths:\n\n**Path A — Sysadmin links system template to SOP**:\n```\nPATCH /templates/:id  { sop_id: \"<sop-uuid>\" }\n  → System template now references an SOP\n  → All future company copies will inherit this link\n  → Existing company templates need manual update or re-copy\n```\n\n**Path B — Automatic during SOP Manager sync**:\n```\nsop_manager.py matches SOPs to templates by trade_code:\n  1. Find SOP with trade_code='PNT' and task_name='Interior Painting'\n  2. Find system template with matching trade\n  3. UPDATE work_order_templates SET sop_id = sop.id\n```\n\n### 5.2 What the Link Provides\n\nOnce a template has `sop_id`, the system can:\n- Display SOP metadata on the template detail page\n- List all procedure steps for the template\n- Initialize step-level tracking when a work order is created\n- Provide detailed instructions to field workers\n- Enable the timesheet app to know what steps exist for duration tracking\n\n---\n\n## 6. Unit Work Order Lifecycle\n\n### 6.1 Creation\n\nA unit work order is created from a project-scope template:\n\n```\nPOST /work-orders\n  {\n    template_id: \"<project-template-uuid>\",\n    organization_id: \"...\",\n    project_id: \"...\",\n    assigned_to: \"...\",\n    ...\n  }\n```\n\nAt this point, the work order exists but has no step progress records.\n\n### 6.2 Step Initialization\n\nWhen work begins, step progress records are created:\n\n```\nPOST /work-orders/:id/initialize-steps\n  1. Resolve sop_id from template (with inheritance)\n  2. Fetch all sop_steps for that SOP\n  3. Check no existing progress records (idempotency guard)\n  4. Create one work_order_step_progress row per sop_step:\n     {\n       work_order_id: wo.id,\n       sop_step_id: step.id,\n       status: 'pending',\n       organization_id: wo.organization_id\n     }\n  5. Return { initialized: N }\n```\n\nThis is a one-time operation per work order. Calling it again returns HTTP 409.\n\n### 6.3 Step Execution\n\nField workers update step progress as they work:\n\n```\nPATCH /work-orders/step-progress/:id\n  {\n    status: 'in_progress'  →  auto-sets started_at\n    status: 'completed'    →  auto-sets completed_at\n    duration_minutes: 45   →  actual time spent (key for timesheets)\n    notes: \"Used 2 coats instead of 1\"\n    photo_urls: [\"https://...\"]\n  }\n```\n\n### 6.4 Step Status Flow\n\n```\npending ──▶ in_progress ──▶ completed\n   │              │\n   │              └──▶ blocked (waiting on dependency)\n   │\n   └──▶ skipped (not applicable to this WO)\n```\n\n### 6.5 Step Overrides\n\nIf a work order needs to deviate from the canonical SOP step:\n\n```\nPATCH /work-orders/step-progress/:id\n  {\n    override_detail: \"Customer requested oil-based primer instead of latex\",\n    is_override: true\n  }\n```\n\nThe original SOP step content remains in `sop_steps`. The override is stored locally on the progress record. This enables:\n- Reconciliation reports (what deviated from SOP)\n- Continuous SOP improvement (common overrides suggest SOP updates needed)\n- Audit trails for quality assurance\n\n---\n\n## 7. Step Progress Tracking\n\n### 7.1 Data Structure\n\nEach `work_order_step_progress` row captures:\n\n| Field | Type | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `work_order_id` | UUID | Which work order |\n| `sop_step_id` | UUID | Which SOP step (links to canonical procedure) |\n| `status` | TEXT | pending / in_progress / completed / skipped / blocked |\n| `completed_by` | UUID | Which user completed this step |\n| `started_at` | TIMESTAMP | When work began on this step |\n| `completed_at` | TIMESTAMP | When work finished |\n| `duration_minutes` | INTEGER | **Actual time spent** (primary timesheet input) |\n| `notes` | TEXT | Worker observations, deviations |\n| `photo_urls` | TEXT[] | Evidence photos |\n| `override_detail` | TEXT | Custom instructions replacing SOP step |\n| `is_override` | BOOLEAN | Flag for reconciliation reporting |\n| `organization_id` | UUID | Tenant isolation (RLS) |\n\n### 7.2 Duration Tracking Rules\n\n- **Employees**: MUST record `duration_minutes` for every completed step. This is the basis for timesheet generation.\n- **Sub-contractors**: Duration tracking is OPTIONAL by default. Some sub-contractors are paid by completed work (not hours), so duration is informational only. Exceptions exist where hour tracking is required — this is configured at the contract level in the timesheet app.\n\n### 7.3 Querying Progress\n\n```\nGET /work-orders/:id/step-progress\n\nReturns:\n[\n  {\n    id: \"progress-uuid\",\n    work_order_id: \"wo-uuid\",\n    sop_step_id: \"step-uuid\",\n    status: \"completed\",\n    duration_minutes: 45,\n    completed_by: \"user-uuid\",\n    started_at: \"2026-03-09T08:00:00Z\",\n    completed_at: \"2026-03-09T08:45:00Z\",\n    sop_step: {\n      phase_name: \"Surface Preparation\",\n      phase_number: 1,\n      step_number: 2,\n      step_name: \"Clean Surfaces\",\n      tasks_summary: \"Remove dust, grease, mildew per SSPC-SP1\",\n      est_duration_minutes: 30\n    }\n  },\n  ...\n]\n```\n\nThe joined `sop_step` data provides context without requiring a separate SOP lookup.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Timesheet App Integration\n\n### 8.1 Data Contract\n\nThe timesheet app (separate application) reads `work_order_step_progress` to build employee timesheets. The contract is:\n\n```sql\nSELECT\n    wosp.completed_by,\n    wosp.duration_minutes,\n    wosp.started_at,\n    wosp.completed_at,\n    wosp.status,\n    wo.project_id,\n    wo.template_id,\n    ss.phase_name,\n    ss.step_name,\n    ss.est_duration_minutes,\n    s.trade_code,\n    s.trade_name,\n    s.task_name\nFROM work_order_step_progress wosp\nJOIN work_orders wo ON wo.id = wosp.work_order_id\nJOIN sop_steps ss ON ss.id = wosp.sop_step_id\nJOIN sops s ON s.id = ss.sop_id\nWHERE wosp.status = 'completed'\n  AND wosp.completed_by = :user_id\n  AND wosp.completed_at BETWEEN :period_start AND :period_end\nORDER BY wosp.completed_at;\n```\n\n### 8.2 Timesheet Generation Flow\n\n```\nwork_order_step_progress (this system)\n    │\n    │  completed steps with duration_minutes\n    │\n    ▼\nTimesheet App reads via Supabase client\n    │\n    ├── Groups by: employee + date + project\n    ├── Sums: duration_minutes per grouping\n    ├── Compares: actual vs estimated (from sop_steps.est_duration_minutes)\n    ├── Flags: overrides (is_override=true) for review\n    │\n    ▼\nTimesheet records (in timesheet app's own tables)\n    │\n    ▼\nPayroll export\n```\n\n### 8.3 Estimated vs Actual Duration\n\nEach `sop_steps` row has `est_duration_minutes` (from the SOP). Each `work_order_step_progress` row has `duration_minutes` (actual). The timesheet app can:\n\n- Flag steps where actual >> estimated (potential inefficiency or SOP underestimate)\n- Flag steps where actual << estimated (potential quality concern or SOP overestimate)\n- Aggregate variance data to improve SOP estimates over time\n\n---\n\n## 9. API Reference\n\nAll endpoints are in `apps/api/src/routes/work-orders.ts`.\n\n### SOP Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/sops` | List active SOPs. Optional filters: `?trade_id=`, `?trade_code=` |\n| `GET` | `/sops/:id` | SOP detail with sections, steps, and dependencies |\n\n### Template-SOP Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/templates/:id/sop` | Get SOP linked to template (with inheritance resolution) |\n| `PATCH` | `/templates/:id` | Update template fields including `sop_id` |\n\n### Step Progress Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/work-orders/:id/step-progress` | Get all step progress for a WO (with joined SOP step data) |\n| `POST` | `/work-orders/:id/initialize-steps` | Create pending progress records from SOP steps (one-time) |\n| `PATCH` | `/work-orders/step-progress/:id` | Update individual step (status, duration, notes, photos) |\n\n### Existing Endpoints (unchanged)\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/templates/assign-to-company` | Copy system → company template (preserves sop_id) |\n| `POST` | `/templates/assign-to-project` | Create project template from company (lazy sop_id) |\n| `GET` | `/templates/project/:projectId` | List project templates (resolves from parents) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Frontend Surfaces\n\n### 10.1 Template Detail Page (`TemplateDetail.tsx`)\n\nDisplays a blue info box when the template has a linked SOP:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  LINKED SOP                         │\n│  PNT-SOP-001  Interior Painting     │\n│  Rev 1.2                            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\nFor project-scope templates, shows whether the SOP was inherited from the parent template.\n\n### 10.2 Work Order Detail Page (`WorkOrderDetail.tsx`)\n\nDisplays a \"Procedure Steps\" panel with:\n\n- **Initialize button**: Appears when no step progress exists. Creates pending records.\n- **Step list**: Each step shows phase name, step number, step name, and status dropdown.\n- **Status colors**: Green (completed), yellow (in progress), white (pending).\n- **Duration display**: Shows recorded minutes when available.\n- **Task summary**: Brief description from the Executive Checklist.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Procedure Steps                                │\n│                                                 │\n│  [Completed ▼] Surface Prep - Step 1:           │\n│                Inspect Surfaces          45m    │\n│                Check for damage, moisture...     │\n│                                                 │\n│  [In Progress ▼] Surface Prep - Step 2:         │\n│                   Clean Surfaces                │\n│                   Remove dust, grease...         │\n│                                                 │\n│  [Pending ▼] Surface Prep - Step 3:             │\n│              Repair Defects                     │\n│              Fill holes, caulk gaps...           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. Edge Cases & Business Rules\n\n### 11.1 SOP Updates After Template Freeze\n\nIf an SOP is updated after a project template is frozen:\n- The frozen template's `sop_id` still points to the same SOP\n- `sop_steps` content may have changed\n- Existing `work_order_step_progress` records still reference the old step IDs\n- **Rule**: SOP updates should create new step records (new UUIDs), not modify existing ones. This preserves the integrity of in-progress work orders.\n\n### 11.2 Template Without SOP\n\nNot all templates require an SOP link. Templates without `sop_id`:\n- Display no SOP section on the detail page\n- Cannot initialize step progress on work orders\n- Work orders function normally but without step-level tracking\n- The timesheet app falls back to WO-level duration tracking\n\n### 11.3 Multiple Phases\n\nAn SOP can have multiple procedure phases (e.g., Removal + Installation). Each phase has its own Executive Checklist with up to 7 steps. Steps are ordered by `phase_number` then `step_number`:\n\n```\nPhase 1: Removal\n  Step 1: Disconnect fixtures\n  Step 2: Remove old piping\n  Step 3: Cap and test\n\nPhase 2: Installation\n  Step 1: Layout and measure\n  Step 2: Install supply lines\n  Step 3: Install drain lines\n  Step 4: Connect fixtures\n  Step 5: Pressure test\n```\n\nAll steps across all phases are initialized as progress records for a single work order.\n\n### 11.4 SOP Dependencies\n\nThe `sop_dependencies` table tracks relationships between SOPs:\n\n| Link Type | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `prerequisite` | Must be completed before this SOP can start |\n| `sub_procedure` | Called inline during a step of this SOP |\n| `cross_reference` | Related but not blocking |\n| `optional` | May be needed depending on conditions |\n\nCurrently informational — displayed in SOP detail views. Future enhancement: enforce prerequisite ordering at the work order level.\n\n### 11.5 RLS (Row-Level Security)\n\n| Table | Policy |\n|---|---|\n| `sop_sections` | Read: all authenticated users. Write: sysadmin only. |\n| `sop_steps` | Read: all authenticated users. Write: sysadmin only. |\n| `sop_dependencies` | Read: all authenticated users. Write: sysadmin only. |\n| `sop_ref_docs` | Read: all authenticated users. Write: sysadmin only. |\n| `work_order_step_progress` | Read/Write: tenant-isolated by `organization_id`. Sysadmin: full access. |\n\nSOPs are global knowledge — any authenticated user can read them. Step progress is tenant-isolated — users only see their organization's data.\n\n### 11.6 Idempotency Guards\n\n- `POST /work-orders/:id/initialize-steps`: Returns HTTP 409 if steps already exist. Safe to retry.\n- `PATCH /work-orders/step-progress/:id`: Idempotent — setting the same status twice is a no-op (timestamps only set on first transition).\n- SOP Manager sync: Deletes and re-inserts sections/steps. Idempotent by design.\n\n---\n\n## Appendix: Complete Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\n                    ┌──────────────────────┐\n                    │  SOP Markdown Files   │\n                    │  (Git repository)     │\n                    └──────────┬───────────┘\n                               │\n                    sop_manager.py parse\n                               │\n                    ┌──────────▼───────────┐\n                    │  sop_ref_docs        │\n                    │  sops                │\n                    │  sop_sections        │\n                    │  sop_steps           │\n                    │  sop_dependencies    │\n                    └──────────┬───────────┘\n                               │\n                    sop_id FK on templates\n                               │\n          ┌────────────────────▼────────────────────┐\n          │         Work Order Templates             │\n          │                                          │\n          │  system ──copy──▶ company ──lazy──▶ project\n          │  (sop_id)        (sop_id)          (sop_id)\n          │                                    (frozen)\n          └────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n              